Why the Health insurance companies should do this
innovative
furthering scientific progress
being able to show off to other companies " we have this you dont."



examples for when studies failed because not enough people

lokal begrenztem Prostatakrebs 2016, 350 out of 2000 people registered

chronischen lymphatischen Leukämie, 2017-2022 86 out of 94 people registered.

Studie zu Lupus nur 21 von 120 geplanten Teilnehmern.




how to implement: flowchart

User button on App (insert photo maybe)

THE USER CLICKS THE button
->
THE USER GETS ASKED IF THEY CONSENT TO USE THEIR DATA TO FIND
STUDIES THAT HE THEY ARE ELIGIBLE TO
->
THE USER CLICKS YES
->
THE DATA FROM THE EPA GETS CROSS CHECKED WITH OUR AVAILABLE DATA FROM THE TABLE FROM DRKS
->
HOW? FIND OUT NEXT EPISODE// TENTATIVE
->
THE USER GETS A LIST OF STUDIES THEY ARE ELIGIBLE FOR
->
THE USER CLICKS ON A STUDY
->
PAGE OPENS ON A NEATLY FORMATTED THING WHICH SHOWS 
-HOW LONG THE STUDY GOES FOR
-A BRIEF DESCRIPTION WHAT THIS TRIAL IS ABOUT
-WHAT KIND OF CRITERIA GOT MATCHED AS TO WHY SHE WAS SHOWN THIS//maybe
-and other stuff idk

->
THE USER CLICKS THE BUTTON TO CONTACT THE PEOPLE FROM THE STUDY
->
USER GETS PROMPTED IF THEY WANT TO SEND AN EMAIL TO SHARE THEIR DATA WITH THE ORGANIZERS OF THE STUDY
->
USER CLICKS YES
->
MAIL HAS BEEN SENT. YOU SHOULD BE GETTING AN ANSWER SOON (hopefully)


gpt:
User clicks button on the app and consents to share data for study matching.

Data is cross-checked with available studies in the DRKS database.// with a RAG //

User receives a list of eligible studies, clicks to view details.

Study page shows details (duration, description, criteria match).

User clicks to contact study organizers and confirms sending email.

Confirmation message: "Email sent. You should be getting an answer soon."

